hwMplsOam.description: The HUAWEI-MPLSOAM-MIB contains objects to configure OAM module. The Operation, Administration and Maintenance (OAM) is an effective means for decreasing the cost of network maintenance. The MPLS OAM is used to administrate and maintain MPLS.
hwMplsOam.name: hwMplsOam

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelAutoOvertime.description: If the oam receives CV/FFD, it records the parameters included in the packet, such as OAM type and frequency. If the oam does not receive any CV/FFD packet before the timer expires, It will send BDI with dLOCV defect.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelAutoOvertime.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelAutoOvertime

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelAva.description: This notification is generated when the CO-ROUTE is found in the unavailable state.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelAva.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelAva

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelBDIFreq.description: BDI is generated at the trail termination source point of a return path in response to a defect detected at the trail termination sink point of an LSP in the forwarding direction. The frequency of BDI can be set by user. 1: per-second; 2: same as detect frequency.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelBDIFreq.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelBDIFreq

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelBdiDefectTyp.description: 0: no defect; 1: dServer, 2: dPeerMe, 3: dLOCV, Loss of Connectivity Verification defect; 4: dTTSI-Mismatch, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismatch defect; 5: dTTSI-Mismerge, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismerge defect.; 6: dExcess, Receiving excess rate of CV/FFD; 7: dUnknown, Unknown defect in the MPLS network. 8: dOamFail, AutoProtocal timer expires.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelBdiDefectTyp.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelBdiDefectType

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelCompatibilit.description: 1: Ptn-Mode; 2: RouterMode; Valid only for the bidirectional tunnel configuration.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelCompatibilit.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelCompatibilityMode

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDefectType.description: 0: no defect; 1: dServer, 2: dPeerMe, 3: dLOCV, Loss of Connectivity Verification defect; 4: dTTSI-Mismatch, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismatch defect; 5: dTTSI-Mismerge, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismerge defect.; 6: dExcess, Receiving excess rate of CV/FFD; 7: dUnknown, Unknown defect in the MPLS network. 8: dOamFail, AutoProtocal timer expires. 9: corouteDown, coroute down.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDefectType.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDefectType

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDetFreq.description: For CV: the frequency is static, per second. For FFD: the frequency is set by user. The value can be 10ms, 20ms, 50ms,100ms,200ms,500ms,3ms. Any other frequency is wrong. 0: 1000ms(only for cv); 1: 10ms; 2: 20ms; 3: 50ms; 4: 100ms; 5: 200ms; 6: 500ms; 7: 3ms.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDetFreq.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDetFreq

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDetType.description: There are two types of OAM packets, CV and FFD. 1: CV; 2: FFD.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDetType.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelDetType

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by binding the tunnel ifindex.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelEntry.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelEntry

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelInDefect.description: This notification is generated when the CO-ROUTE is found not in the defect state.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelInDefect.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelInDefect

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelIndex.description: This is a unique index for an OAM entry in the OAM table.

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelOutDefect.description: This notification is generated when the CO-ROUTE is found not in the defect state.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelOutDefect.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelOutDefect

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelReceiveEnabl.description: 0: The OAM Receive function is Disabled; 1: The OAM Receive function is Eabled;
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelReceiveEnabl.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelReceiveEnable

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelRevDetFreq.description: For CV: the frequency is static, per second. For FFD: the frequency is set by user. The value can be 10ms, 20ms, 50ms,100ms,200ms,500ms,3ms. Any other frequency is wrong. 0: 1000ms(only for cv); 1: 10ms; 2: 20ms; 3: 50ms; 4: 100ms; 5: 200ms; 6: 500ms; 7: invalid; 8: 3ms.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelRevDetFreq.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelRevDetFreq

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and delete a row in this table.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelRowStatus.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelRowStatus

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelSendEnable.description: 0: The OAM Send function is Disabled; 1: The OAM Send function is Eabled;
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelSendEnable.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelSendEnable

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelTable.description: This table specifies Static Co-Route MPLS OAM capability and associated information, such as DetType and DetFrequence.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelTable.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelTable

hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelUnAva.description: This notification is generated when the CO-ROUTE is found in the unavailable state.
hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelUnAva.name: hwMplsOamBidirectionalTunnelUnAva

hwMplsOamCapability.description: Whether OAM is globally capable. 0: incapable; 1: capable; 2: capable(based-itu); The default value is incapable.
hwMplsOamCapability.name: hwMplsOamCapability

hwMplsOamEgrAutoEn.description: If autoprotocol, then the egress can process extended FDI sent by ingress. 0: disable; 1: enable; Valid only for the egress configuration.
hwMplsOamEgrAutoEn.name: hwMplsOamEgrAutoEn

hwMplsOamEgrAutoOvertime.description: This time is set at the egress. If the egress receives CV/FFD, it records the parameters included in the packet, such as OAM type and frequency. If the egress does not receive any OAM packet before the timer expires, the sink LSR will send BDI with dLOCV defect. Valid only for the egress configuration.
hwMplsOamEgrAutoOvertime.name: hwMplsOamEgrAutoOvertime

hwMplsOamEgrAutoProFDI.description: The FDI packet is used by the upstream node in an LSP to inform the egress of the defect information. It is also generated when the auto protocol is enabled, with which the LSP ingress notifies the egress to stop the OAM detection.
hwMplsOamEgrAutoProFDI.name: hwMplsOamEgrAutoProFDI

hwMplsOamEgrAvaState.description: If the LSP Timer (T1) expires, then the LSP enters the Unavailable state. The start point of the Unavailable state is deemed to be at the entry into the LSP defect state. An LSP re-enters the Available state after the LSP Defect State. first exists. T1 defines the length of time the LSP is in the Defect state before declaring an LSP Unavailable or returning to defect free state 0: available state; 1: unavailable state.
hwMplsOamEgrAvaState.name: hwMplsOamEgrAvaState

hwMplsOamEgrBDIFreq.description: BDI is generated at the trail termination source point of a return path in response to a defect detected at the trail termination sink point of an LSP in the forwarding direction. The frequency of BDI can be set by user. Only valid for egress configuration. The default value is detect frequency and it is valid only when a backward-LSP exists. 0: per-second; 1: same as detect frequency.
hwMplsOamEgrBDIFreq.name: hwMplsOamEgrBDIFreq

hwMplsOamEgrDefectType.description: 0: no defect; 1: dServer, 2: dPeerMe, 3: dLOCV, Loss of Connectivity Verification defect; 4: dTTSI-Mismatch, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismatch defect; 5: dTTSI-Mismerge, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismerge defect.; 6: dExcess, Receiving excess rate of CV/FFD; 7: dUnknown, Unknown defect in the MPLS network. 8: dOamFail, AutoProtocal timer expires. 9: dEgressDown.
hwMplsOamEgrDefectType.name: hwMplsOamEgrDefectType

hwMplsOamEgrDetType.description: 0: invalid, if auto-protocol, this detect type is invalid; 1: CV; 2: FFD.
hwMplsOamEgrDetType.name: hwMplsOamEgrDetType

hwMplsOamEgrEnable.description: Whether one LSP is enabled with OAM. If disable, LSP is not monitored; If enable, CV/FFD is generated at the source LSR of the LSP and checked at the sink LSR of the LSP, and user can set other configuration. 0: The OAM function is disabled on the egress; 1: The OAM function is enabled on the egress.
hwMplsOamEgrEnable.name: hwMplsOamEgrEnable

hwMplsOamEgrEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by an LSR for every LSP capable of supporting MPLS OAM at egress.
hwMplsOamEgrEntry.name: hwMplsOamEgrEntry

hwMplsOamEgrFirstPkt.description: If autoprotocol is enabled, this notification is generated when egress receives the first CV/FFD packet.
hwMplsOamEgrFirstPkt.name: hwMplsOamEgrFirstPkt

hwMplsOamEgrLSPAva.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found in the available state at the LSP egress.
hwMplsOamEgrLSPAva.name: hwMplsOamEgrLSPAva

hwMplsOamEgrLSPInDefect.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found in the defect state at the LSP egress.
hwMplsOamEgrLSPInDefect.name: hwMplsOamEgrLSPInDefect

hwMplsOamEgrLSPOutDefect.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found not in the defect state at the LSP egress.
hwMplsOamEgrLSPOutDefect.name: hwMplsOamEgrLSPOutDefect

hwMplsOamEgrLSPUnAva.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found in the unavailable state at the LSP egress.
hwMplsOamEgrLSPUnAva.name: hwMplsOamEgrLSPUnAva

hwMplsOamEgrLspName.description: The object indicates the name of static LSP at egress.
hwMplsOamEgrLspName.name: hwMplsOamEgrLspName

hwMplsOamEgrLsrId.description: The object indicates the Ingress LSR ID of the LSP.
hwMplsOamEgrLsrId.name: hwMplsOamEgrLsrId

hwMplsOamEgrRevTunnName.description: The object indicates the name of a reverse tunnel.
hwMplsOamEgrRevTunnName.name: hwMplsOamEgrRevTunnName

hwMplsOamEgrRevType.description: When an LSP is found to be in defect, the sink LSR of the LSP should send BDI to inform the source LSR of the LSP,the BDI is transferred through the reverse LSP. The type of reverse LSP can be private or shared. If private, then the reverse LSP can be used only when the only LSP in defect; If shared, the reverse LSP, which is shared between many forward LSPs that have the same source LSRs and sink LSRs. 0: invalid, when the reverse LSR does not exist; 1: private; 2: share.
hwMplsOamEgrRevType.name: hwMplsOamEgrRevType

hwMplsOamEgrRlsnDown.description: This notification is generated when the Rlsn is down.
hwMplsOamEgrRlsnDown.name: hwMplsOamEgrRlsnDown

hwMplsOamEgrRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and delete a row in this table.
hwMplsOamEgrRowStatus.name: hwMplsOamEgrRowStatus

hwMplsOamEgrSessTunnId.description: The object indicates the the Ingress session tunnel ID of the LSP..
hwMplsOamEgrSessTunnId.name: hwMplsOamEgrSessTunnId

hwMplsOamEgrTable.description: This table specifies per-LSP MPLS OAM capability and associated information, such as DetectType, DetectFrequency.
hwMplsOamEgrTable.name: hwMplsOamEgrTable

hwMplsOamIgrAvaState.description: If the LSP Timer (T1) expires, then the LSP enters the Unavailable state. The start point of the Unavailable state is deemed to be at the entry into the LSP defect state. An LSP re-enters the Available state after the LSP Defect state exists first. T1 defines the length of time the LSP is in the Defect state before declaring an LSP Unavailable or returning to defect free state. 0: available state; 1: unavailable state.
hwMplsOamIgrAvaState.name: hwMplsOamIgrAvaState

hwMplsOamIgrBDIFreq.description: BDI is generated at the trail termination source point of a return path in response to a defect detected at the trail termination sink point of an LSP in the forwarding direction. The frequency of BDI can be set by user. 1: per-second; 2: same as detect frequency.
hwMplsOamIgrBDIFreq.name: hwMplsOamIgrBDIFreq

hwMplsOamIgrCompatibilityMode.description: 1: Ptn-Mode; 2: Router-Mode; Valid only for the ingress configuration.
hwMplsOamIgrCompatibilityMode.name: hwMplsOamIgrCompatibilityMode

hwMplsOamIgrDefectType.description: Defect is defined as interruption of the capability of a transport entity (e.g., network connection) to transfer user or OAM information. There are six types of defect: 0: no defect; 1: dServer; 2: dPeerMe; 3: dLOCV, Loss of Connectivity Verification defect; 4: dTTSI-Mismatch, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismatch defect; 5: dTTSI-Mismerge, Trail Termination Source Identifier Mismerge defect; 6: dExcess, Receiving excess rate of CV/FFD; 7: dUnknown, Unknown defect in the MPLS network.. 8: dOamFail, AutoProtocal timer expires. 9: dIngressDown.
hwMplsOamIgrDefectType.name: hwMplsOamIgrDefectType

hwMplsOamIgrDetFreq.description: For CV: the frequency is static, per second. For FFD: the frequency is set by user. The value can be 10ms, 20ms, 50ms,100ms,200ms,500ms,3ms. Any other frequency is wrong. 0: 1000ms(only for cv); 1: 10ms; 2: 20ms; 3: 50ms; 4: 100ms; 5: 200ms; 6: 500ms; 7: 3ms.
hwMplsOamIgrDetFreq.name: hwMplsOamIgrDetFreq

hwMplsOamIgrDetType.description: There are two types of OAM packets, CV and FFD. The CV flow is generated at the source LSR of the LSP with a nominal frequency of 1/s and terminated at the sink LSR of the LSP. FFD provides failure detection option for an LSP independent of the CV based availability model and is not tied to the CV insertion rate. Insertion rates at 1/s or faster may also be used. The CV/FFD packet contains a network-unique identifier (TTSI) so that all types of defects can be detected. 1: CV; 2: FFD.
hwMplsOamIgrDetType.name: hwMplsOamIgrDetType

hwMplsOamIgrEnable.description: Whether one LSP is OAM enable. If disable, LSP is not monitored; If enable, CV/FFD is generated at the source LSR of the LSP and checked at the sink LSR of the LSP,and user can set other configuration. 0: The OAM function is disabled on the ingress; 1: The OAM function is enabled on the ingress.
hwMplsOamIgrEnable.name: hwMplsOamIgrEnable

hwMplsOamIgrEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by an LSR for every LSP capable of supporting MPLS OAM at ingress.
hwMplsOamIgrEntry.name: hwMplsOamIgrEntry

hwMplsOamIgrIndex.description: The interface index of the detected tunnel.
hwMplsOamIgrIndex.name: hwMplsOamIgrIndex

hwMplsOamIgrLSPAva.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found in the available state at the LSP ingress.
hwMplsOamIgrLSPAva.name: hwMplsOamIgrLSPAva

hwMplsOamIgrLSPInDefect.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found in the defect state at the LSP ingress.
hwMplsOamIgrLSPInDefect.name: hwMplsOamIgrLSPInDefect

hwMplsOamIgrLSPOutDefect.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found not in the defect state at the LSP ingress.
hwMplsOamIgrLSPOutDefect.name: hwMplsOamIgrLSPOutDefect

hwMplsOamIgrLSPUnAva.description: This notification is generated when the LSP is found in the unavailable state at the LSP ingress.
hwMplsOamIgrLSPUnAva.name: hwMplsOamIgrLSPUnAva

hwMplsOamIgrRevLspName.description: The object indicates name of the reverse LSP.
hwMplsOamIgrRevLspName.name: hwMplsOamIgrRevLspName

hwMplsOamIgrRevLsrId.description: Only for ingress, the object indicates the ingress LSR ID of the reverse LSP,, expressed in IP address.
hwMplsOamIgrRevLsrId.name: hwMplsOamIgrRevLsrId

hwMplsOamIgrRevSessTunnId.description: Only for ingress, the object indicates the session tunnel ID of the reverse LSP.
hwMplsOamIgrRevSessTunnId.name: hwMplsOamIgrRevSessTunnId

hwMplsOamIgrRevType.description: When an LSP is found to be in defect, the sink LSR if the LSP should send BDI to inform the source LSR of the LSP, the BDI is transferred through the reverse LSP. The type of reverse LSP can be private or shared. If private, then the reverse LSP can be used only when the only LSP is in defect; If shared, the reverse LSP which is shared between many forward LSPs, whose source LSRs are the same and sink LSRs are the same. 1: private; 2: share.
hwMplsOamIgrRevType.name: hwMplsOamIgrRevType

hwMplsOamIgrRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and delete a row in this table.
hwMplsOamIgrRowStatus.name: hwMplsOamIgrRowStatus

hwMplsOamIgrTunnName.description: The name of a tunnel. For ingress, it means the tunnel name of the detected LSP. For egress, it means the tunnel name of the reverse LSP.
